President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday  evening met behind closed doors with the leadership of the National Assembly.The meeting which was held at the Presidential Villa, Abuja started at about 9.10pm with the arrival of the President. Speaking to State House correspondents after the meeting, Senate President, Bukola Saraki said they discussed a variety of topics ranging from budget to national issues. He , however  said the lawmakers didn’t not discuss the electoral act amendement bill which proposes reordering of elections sequence Recall that the President had recently rejected the Electoral Act amendement bill and Peace Corps Bill. The House of Reps had threatened to override the president on the Peace Corps Bill.   Those who attended the meeting from the National Assembly included the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara; his deputy, Lasun Yusuf; Senate Leader, Ahmed Lawan; House Leader, Femi Gbajabiamila; Senator Sola Adeyeye, Philip Aduda, House Chief Whip,  Al-Hassan Dogowa, and  Deputy Whip, Pally Iriase among others. Buhari was joined from the Executive arm of government by his Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari; Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha; Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina; Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu and Senior Special Assistant to the President on National Assembly Matters (Senate), Senator Ita Enang.